post_text: College Place Public Schools got the green light from the Walla Walla County Department of Community Health to begin planning for a hybrid return to school onsite as early as October 19th. CPPS previously approved an "AM/PM Hybrid Model" for when they got the go ahead from health officials. The board will meet to discuss the plan as CPPS anticipates a district wide PK-12 return in the hybrid mode as soon as it safe to do so.

CPHS Families: If you received a laptop that does not have a built in web camera yesterday by mistake at CPHS please come to the high school to pick up a camera for the device today, you will need that feature for participation in courses. We will be set up again today in the CPHS Stadium parking lot from 8am-3pm. If that does not work for you please exchange it next week, Tues-Thurs at the high school office between 8am-4pm. Sorry for the inconvenience.

Familias de CPHS: Si recibió una computadora portátil que no tiene una cámara web incorporada ayer por error en CPHS, por favor venga a la escuela secundaria a recoger una cámara para el dispositivo hoy, necesitará esa función para participar en los cursos. Estaremos instalados nuevamente hoy en el estacionamiento del estadio CPHS de 8 am a 3 pm. Si eso no funciona para usted, cámbielo la próxima semana, de martes a jueves en la oficina de la escuela secundaria entre las 8 am y las 4 pm. Lo siento por los inconvenientes ocasionados.

El plazo para solicitar el EBT pandémico (P-EBT) se extendió hasta el 11 de Septiembre de 2020!

P-EBT ayuda a las familias con fondos para cubrir el costo de las comidas mientras la escuela está cerrada. Este beneficio es para los niños de Washington, incluidos los niños de hogares de inmigrantes, en los grados K-12 que reciben comidas escolares gratuitas o a precio reducido.

Aplicar en línea: www.WashingtonConnection.org O llame al: 877-501-2233 (DSHS servicios de interpretación están disponibles)

post_text:
Pandemic EBT (P-EBT) Deadline Extended to September 11, 2020!

P-EBT provides families with funds to make up for the cost of meals while school is closed. This benefit is for Washington children, including children of immigrant households, in grades K-12 who receive free or reduced-price school meals.

Apply Online: www.WashingtonConnection.org Or Call: 877–501–2233 (DSHS Customer Service — interpreter services are available)

post_text:
In a special session held tonight the CPPS Board of Directors voted to move the start of the 2020-2021 school year back to begin September 8, 2020. This is an effort to give quality time to prepare for a full return to school in the fall.

Adobe Certified Associates

Congratulations to the following Media Communications Class Producers and Talon Yearbook Editors and Designers for passing the challenging Adobe Certification Exam: Gissel Luna 12, Alondra Gutierrez 10, Samanta Valladares 12, Kaitlyn Morrison 12, Michael Perot 12, Maddy Neil 11, Kelli Meza 10, Garrett Green 12, Nina Smith 12.

Adobe Certified Associate (ACA) certification is an industry-recognized credential that effectively validates one’s skills in Adobe digital-media software.

They tested in the following programs:
Digital Video Production with Premiere Pro
Visual Design with Photoshop
Print and Digital Media Publication with Indesign

🧡💙Over 50 CPHS seniors still need a yearbook. The yearbook is filled with artistic student photos and interviews from our student body. Advanced Media produced HP Reveal videos! This years book tells the true story of this year. The HOCO dance, spirit days and the assemblies where Seniors earned the coveted Spirit stick four years in a row! This year was packed with good times and we want Seniors to remember their senior year was more than COVID-19. Yearbook Staffers told the stories in the Talon Yearbook and students can look back for years to come, into adulthood and view the real stories of 2020 Senior year. Please consider donating a book to a Senior in need. www.jostensyearbooks.com select CPHS and in the name field “Senior” for the first name and “Donation” as last name.
Four yearbooks have been donated so far 🧡💙

Follow @cphshawks_ybk on Instagram

post_text:
A press release from the Walla Walla County Auditor- Mistakes to ballots in College Place. Please check your ballots.

October 23, 2019

To: News Media and Political Parties

From: Karen Martin, Walla Walla County Auditor

Subject: November 5, 2019 General Election

Ballot mailing delay to City of College Place precincts

Due to a clerical error, ballots mailed to voters in the College Place 4 and College Place 5 precincts were the wrong ballot type.

Replacement ballots with the correct type are being mailed to the 1,885 voters in these 2 precincts. Voters in these precincts may also request a replacement ballot from our office.

If the voter has already returned the original ballot, it will be held pending receipt of the replacement ballot.

No other precincts were impacted by this error.
